reviews.text: Not particularly crowded. A relatively small and comfortable shopping mall in the locality.
It is conveniently located near HKU MTR exit C2. It has a big Wellcome store together with many other shops.
Mall has some good Chinese and Japanese restaurants...

It has quite a few eating joints. My favourites are Panash Bakery and of course Mc D.. on the first floor you can shop apparel and shoes.. actually only one shop for apparel which is Baleno, and a couple of shops for shoes like dr. Kong, etc.. on the second floor is a book shop, a music shop and a few other shops.. they have a game arcade as well on the top floor.. And a supermarket as well.. so basically its a family place..you'll find something for all the age group...
Nice little mall with lots of basic shopping options.  Also has occasional toy or game events.
